explain basic
with cte(a) as (select 1 from dual union all select 2 from dual), cte_1(b) as (select 1 from dual union all select * from cte) select * from cte_1;
Query Plan
======================
|ID|OPERATOR    |NAME|
----------------------
|0 |UNION ALL   |    |
|1 | EXPRESSION |    |
|2 | UNION ALL  |    |
|3 |  EXPRESSION|    |
|4 |  EXPRESSION|    |
======================

Outputs & filters: 
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([UNION(1, UNION(1, 2))]), filter(nil)
  1 - output([1]), filter(nil)
      values({1})
  2 - output([UNION(1, 2)]), filter(nil)
  3 - output([1]), filter(nil)
      values({1})
  4 - output([2]), filter(nil)
      values({2})

with cte(a) as (select 1 from dual union all select 2 from dual), cte_1(b) as (select 1 from dual union all select * from cte) select * from cte_1;
